edu.stanford.nlp.pipeline

Class DocDateAnnotator

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.nlp.pipeline.DocDateAnnotator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Annotator

    public class DocDateAnnotator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Annotator
    Find and record a document (authoring) date for a document. This document date can be used, for instance, in resolving time expressions like "next Thursday". The document date can be today, passed in via a property, given by a filename to date mapping file, or it may be extracted from a filename by regex. The document date is stored as a YYYY-MM-DD String under the CoreAnnotations.DocDateAnnotation key.
    Author:
    Sebastian Schuster
